This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) methods in the biomedical domain. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural network algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning and fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions text classification and temporal relation extraction, which are tasks related to information retrieval and could fall under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the generation of medical data artificially, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
